1
00:02:06,741 --> 00:02:09,981
Mom, coffee! -Coming!

2
00:02:15,901 --> 00:02:17,541
Come, come, come.

3
00:02:20,301 --> 00:02:22,421
Mom,
you have a letter from Punjab.

4
00:02:38,941 --> 00:02:40,701
I won't be able to go there.

5
00:02:40,941 --> 00:02:42,741
Why don't you go to Punjab, dear?

6
00:02:42,901 --> 00:02:45,821
Why? What will I do there?

7
00:02:45,941 --> 00:02:47,821
They've invited us after
such a long time.

8
00:02:47,901 --> 00:02:49,301
It's a kid's birthday.

9
00:02:49,381 --> 00:02:51,821
If I go there, they will start
talking about the past.

10
00:02:51,901 --> 00:02:54,021
That I ran away and got
married to a foreigner.

11
00:02:54,181 --> 00:02:57,421
They will taunt me too, because
my marriage didn't last long.

12
00:02:58,061 --> 00:03:00,381
They are your mother's family
after all. -You should go there.

13
00:03:00,821 --> 00:03:02,261
But mom, all alone?

14
00:03:02,581 --> 00:03:03,861
I won't go there alone.

15
00:03:04,101 --> 00:03:05,221
Don't go there alone.

16
00:03:05,781 --> 00:03:07,461
Take Kash, Kashmir with you.

17
00:03:08,741 --> 00:03:10,381
And who will convince Kash?

18
00:03:15,221 --> 00:03:17,861
Nope. I won't take to her.

19
00:03:44,461 --> 00:03:46,541
Hey.. -Hey!

20
00:03:48,181 --> 00:03:49,941
We've received a letter
from mom's village.

21
00:03:50,021 --> 00:03:51,621
Oh, I see. After all these years?

22
00:03:52,021 --> 00:03:53,021
What does it say?

23
00:04:00,821 --> 00:04:02,861
They have asked her
to visit Punjab.

24
00:04:03,181 --> 00:04:04,421
So Manjeeti will be going?

25
00:04:05,861 --> 00:04:07,021
No.

26
00:04:07,221 --> 00:04:10,461
She wants us to go.

27
00:04:11,821 --> 00:04:13,421
What will I do there?

28
00:04:19,461 --> 00:04:22,141
Exactly! That's what I told her.

29
00:04:22,541 --> 00:04:23,941
We have no reason to.

30
00:04:24,021 --> 00:04:26,381
And we don't know anyone
there either.

31
00:04:31,021 --> 00:04:32,381
Would you like some coffee?

32
00:04:32,821 --> 00:04:33,821
Yes.

33
00:04:46,901 --> 00:04:48,181
Johnson!

34
00:04:48,421 --> 00:04:50,221
Oh, great timing.

35
00:04:50,421 --> 00:04:51,861
You're very welcome.

36
00:04:52,421 --> 00:04:54,061
How's the book coming along?

37
00:04:54,181 --> 00:04:58,021
Well..
capture 33, struggling for it.

38
00:04:58,221 --> 00:04:59,221
Hi, dad.

39
00:04:59,661 --> 00:05:01,461
Hi, darling. -Hey!

40
00:05:04,621 --> 00:05:06,141
Oh my God, that's my favourite.

41
00:05:06,861 --> 00:05:08,141
Hey, what the hell!

42
00:05:08,421 --> 00:05:09,621
Excuse me?

43
00:05:09,701 --> 00:05:10,981
You've been playing all day.
-But it is now..

44
00:05:11,061 --> 00:05:13,021
Give me it! -My turn! Stop it!

45
00:05:13,101 --> 00:05:14,101
Stop!

46
00:05:14,181 --> 00:05:16,141
Dad! Give me that!

47
00:05:16,541 --> 00:05:17,621
Dad! -I said stop!

48
00:05:17,821 --> 00:05:20,421
Dad! -What the hell! -Give
me it! -Stop it!

49
00:05:20,541 --> 00:05:22,701
Again fighting over games. -I'm
seriously gonna smack you now.

50
00:05:22,781 --> 00:05:24,981
Give me that! -Dad! -Stop it!

51
00:05:25,941 --> 00:05:28,701
Kash, you should go to Punjab.

52
00:05:30,301 --> 00:05:32,901
No way. I'm not going anywhere.

53
00:05:34,141 --> 00:05:36,381
Girl, girl..excuse me.

54
00:05:36,941 --> 00:05:38,661
Take that, loser.

55
00:05:40,821 --> 00:05:41,981
Well, go.

56
00:05:42,861 --> 00:05:44,781
Take it as a trip or something.

57
00:05:44,861 --> 00:05:47,141
Dad, I don't need to.
I won't go there.

58
00:05:48,221 --> 00:05:49,301
Kash!

59
00:05:53,341 --> 00:05:55,541
If you really care so
much about Manjeeti..

60
00:05:55,861 --> 00:05:57,301
..then why did you divorce her?

61
00:05:57,541 --> 00:05:59,061
You shouldn't have divorced her.

62
00:06:16,941 --> 00:06:18,021
Thank you.

63
00:06:19,061 --> 00:06:20,061
You okay, no?

64
00:06:20,141 --> 00:06:22,061
Yeah, dear?
-Be kind to your mother.

65
00:06:22,861 --> 00:06:25,221
Anything else?
She's not my mother.

66
00:06:25,861 --> 00:06:27,301
She is Nicole's mother.

67
00:06:29,741 --> 00:06:31,061
Have a safe trip.

68
00:06:31,141 --> 00:06:33,461
And don't talk to strangers.

69
00:06:33,861 --> 00:06:36,261
Let's go, already.
Aren't you done yet?

70
00:06:36,381 --> 00:06:38,861
Don't blame me if we
miss the flight.

71
00:06:39,261 --> 00:06:42,141
Ask Kash to dress appropriately
there.

72
00:06:42,221 --> 00:06:44,821
Well, why don't you try
telling that to her?

73
00:06:45,141 --> 00:06:48,261
Okay then, I'll get going.

74
00:06:49,621 --> 00:06:51,181
Bye, mom. Take care.

75
00:06:55,621 --> 00:06:59,021
Both of you, don't go for a
coffee or something now.

76
00:06:59,101 --> 00:07:00,821
Go back to your respectable
homes.

77
00:07:00,941 --> 00:07:03,821
What's the song,
"When we shall get together.."

78
00:07:03,861 --> 00:07:06,461
Bye! -"There's a lot to share."

79
00:07:06,581 --> 00:07:08,141
No! -Hello!

80
00:07:16,781 --> 00:07:18,461
Father, I won't stay here.

81
00:07:18,661 --> 00:07:20,301
Uncle loves to curse.

82
00:07:21,261 --> 00:07:23,741
Let me come back to the village.
-I'll help in the fields.

83
00:07:23,821 --> 00:07:26,021
I promise. -It's okay,
all uncles love to curse.

84
00:07:26,101 --> 00:07:28,701
Don't worry.
You should work hard, son.

85
00:07:28,781 --> 00:07:30,621
He humiliates me over everything.

86
00:07:30,701 --> 00:07:33,181
You cannot expect any respect
after you get your aunt married.

87
00:07:33,261 --> 00:07:34,861
Don't you hear me curse
your mother's brothers?

88
00:07:34,901 --> 00:07:36,861
Now behave and get to work.

89
00:07:37,421 --> 00:07:39,541
He is afraid of a few curses.

90
00:07:41,101 --> 00:07:42,861
Make your move, already.

91
00:07:42,941 --> 00:07:45,421
Discard a card,
what are you doing?

92
00:07:47,221 --> 00:07:49,181
He never gives the right card.

93
00:07:49,261 --> 00:07:50,621
Phinda? -Yes?

94
00:07:50,701 --> 00:07:52,301
Get me two cold drinks. -Okay.

95
00:07:52,421 --> 00:07:55,421
Sure, go ahead and drink them.
-You don't like to work, do you?

96
00:07:55,541 --> 00:07:56,861
You only enjoy having
cold drinks.

97
00:07:56,941 --> 00:07:59,181
You are kept here on
a salary of 3,500.

98
00:07:59,261 --> 00:08:00,981
And you drink cold drinks
worth 4,000.

99
00:08:01,821 --> 00:08:04,661
Go ahead and drink it. I'll deduct
it from your salary. -Take it.

100
00:08:05,301 --> 00:08:06,301
Take it back.

101
00:08:06,861 --> 00:08:08,421
Too much sweet causes diabetes.

102
00:08:09,701 --> 00:08:11,821
There is an airport pick up
tomorrow. Inform Satta.

103
00:08:12,861 --> 00:08:13,861
Satta!

104
00:08:14,381 --> 00:08:17,061
Listen,
those girls are from Canada.

105
00:08:17,141 --> 00:08:19,661
Ask him to be careful. There
shouldn't be any complaints.

106
00:08:21,421 --> 00:08:22,541
Girls.

107
00:08:23,381 --> 00:08:24,861
From Canada.

108
00:08:25,861 --> 00:08:28,621
If they are from Canada, then
Amrik Singh will pick them up.

109
00:08:33,861 --> 00:08:35,021
Hello, where are you?

110
00:08:35,141 --> 00:08:38,581
I am right here. A red Innova is
parked next to the dustbin.

111
00:08:38,661 --> 00:08:40,901
2985. -We cannot see anyone.

112
00:08:40,981 --> 00:08:43,861
I am walking towards the gate
now. I've gelled my hair.

113
00:08:43,901 --> 00:08:45,621
I am wearing blue jeans.

114
00:08:53,101 --> 00:08:55,781
I'll be damned.

115
00:08:59,661 --> 00:09:01,861
Hot chicks.

116
00:09:03,101 --> 00:09:04,861
I want just one.

117
00:09:16,061 --> 00:09:17,981
Good morning.
-Good morning. -Good morning.

118
00:09:18,061 --> 00:09:19,381
Luggage please.

119
00:09:20,541 --> 00:09:21,741
Excuse me..

120
00:09:22,381 --> 00:09:26,061
I am not a driver. I am the
owner. -But I'll help you ladies.

121
00:09:26,141 --> 00:09:27,901
Just put the luggage in the car.

122
00:09:29,061 --> 00:09:30,301
Okay.

123
00:09:42,421 --> 00:09:43,421
Here.

124
00:09:43,701 --> 00:09:44,741
You too.

125
00:09:44,861 --> 00:09:47,061
I know you must be hungry after
such a long journey.

126
00:09:47,141 --> 00:09:48,221
Take it.

127
00:09:49,581 --> 00:09:51,461
Thanks. -I'll some buy peanuts
on the way too.

128
00:09:52,061 --> 00:09:54,101
Will we manage to reach
without the car moving?

129
00:09:54,181 --> 00:09:57,021
Or will you have to drive it?
-Consider this an aeroplane.

130
00:09:57,301 --> 00:09:58,941
Consider yourself at
the destination.

131
00:10:10,381 --> 00:10:16,421
"I'll buy you a diamond studded
anklets, my love."

132
00:10:18,181 --> 00:10:20,141
Let me share something with you.

133
00:10:20,221 --> 00:10:23,541
You shouldn't tell anyone
that you're from Canada.

134
00:10:23,661 --> 00:10:26,141
People here are as crazy
about Canadians..

135
00:10:26,221 --> 00:10:28,021
..as Discovery Channel
is about snakes.

136
00:10:28,101 --> 00:10:29,101
Oh, God.

137
00:10:29,621 --> 00:10:31,261
You don't need to worry about me.

138
00:10:31,381 --> 00:10:32,861
I am quite chilled.

139
00:10:32,941 --> 00:10:34,701
I am not interested
in going to Canada.

140
00:10:34,821 --> 00:10:37,781
But I would like to give
you a tour of Punjab.

141
00:10:37,861 --> 00:10:40,461
Look at all the green fields.

142
00:10:40,581 --> 00:10:43,821
Filled with golden gems.
I mean wheat.

143
00:10:43,901 --> 00:10:47,141
Look over there, that's a pumping
station. -It is quite useful.

144
00:10:47,221 --> 00:10:49,941
It helps water the fields.
It used to bathe too.

145
00:10:50,021 --> 00:10:51,341
There are many more uses of it.

146
00:10:51,421 --> 00:10:53,061
How did you like our
colourful Punjab?

147
00:10:55,701 --> 00:10:57,541
This is called.. speedbreaker.

148
00:10:58,461 --> 00:11:03,901
"I'll buy you a diamond studded
anklets, my love."

149
00:11:06,621 --> 00:11:09,101
They are here. Come on, everyone.
-They are here.

150
00:11:11,381 --> 00:11:12,381
Come.

151
00:11:13,741 --> 00:11:16,861
There, our daughters are here.

152
00:11:17,461 --> 00:11:19,861
Come here, dear.
-God bless you, dear.

153
00:11:19,901 --> 00:11:22,581
Listen! -Yes? -Judging by the
amount of clothes she is wearing..

154
00:11:22,661 --> 00:11:23,661
Dear, any problem in the way..

155
00:11:23,741 --> 00:11:25,621
..her clothes could have easily
fitted in a pouch.

156
00:11:25,701 --> 00:11:26,981
Why did she bother
carrying a bag?

157
00:11:27,061 --> 00:11:29,581
Wonderful.
Hello, my dear. -Hello.

158
00:11:29,661 --> 00:11:31,101
The other one dresses like us.

159
00:11:31,181 --> 00:11:33,261
How did you like our Punjab?
-At least meet them first.

160
00:11:33,341 --> 00:11:34,981
You can find faults
in them later.

161
00:11:38,221 --> 00:11:40,181
My darling daughters.

162
00:11:40,261 --> 00:11:43,021
I have been yearning
to see you two.

163
00:11:43,101 --> 00:11:45,661
I have waited for you
standing on one foot.

164
00:11:45,741 --> 00:11:47,901
Come on Charno, stop lying.

165
00:11:47,981 --> 00:11:49,821
It's not like they would've
returned..

166
00:11:49,861 --> 00:11:51,301
..if you had waited standing
on both your feet.

167
00:11:51,381 --> 00:11:52,781
How restless of you!

168
00:11:52,861 --> 00:11:56,821
Wonderful! Amazing! My daughters
are finally here.

169
00:11:56,861 --> 00:11:58,381
I am so happy.

170
00:11:58,461 --> 00:12:00,021
She has such curly hair.

171
00:12:00,101 --> 00:12:01,981
God.. there..

172
00:12:02,061 --> 00:12:03,621
Stop it.

173
00:12:03,701 --> 00:12:05,701
Go kids, they are your aunts.
Touch their feet.

174
00:12:05,781 --> 00:12:07,341
Come on kids,
touch the feet of your aunts.

175
00:12:07,421 --> 00:12:08,661
Come on.
-I seek your blessings, aunt.

176
00:12:08,741 --> 00:12:09,861
Go. Come on. -I seek your
blessings, younger aunt.

177
00:12:09,941 --> 00:12:11,941
Hello, aunt. Hello.
-Both of them are very naughty.

178
00:12:12,021 --> 00:12:14,181
Come here. -Hello,
aunt. -Tie your hair first.

179
00:12:14,261 --> 00:12:15,421
Hello. -Tie them up.

180
00:12:15,661 --> 00:12:17,861
They know that we
are their aunts.

181
00:12:18,101 --> 00:12:20,461
Now how about telling us how
is everybody related to us?

182
00:12:20,581 --> 00:12:22,421
Sure, dear. Right away.

183
00:12:22,861 --> 00:12:26,741
Labhu, you stand with your family
on the right. -Okay.

184
00:12:26,981 --> 00:12:28,021
Come on.

185
00:12:29,741 --> 00:12:32,861
Dear, I am your mother's youngest
brother, Ajaib Singh.

186
00:12:32,941 --> 00:12:35,261
She is my wife, Charno.

187
00:12:36,101 --> 00:12:37,781
He is my son, Neeta.

188
00:12:37,861 --> 00:12:40,661
Hello. -He is my grandson, Gopi.

189
00:12:40,741 --> 00:12:43,301
He has come to stay with us.
He is my daughter's son.

190
00:12:43,381 --> 00:12:45,181
Just like you two have.

191
00:12:46,781 --> 00:12:49,701
Labhu, your turn. -Go on.

192
00:12:49,861 --> 00:12:53,021
I am your mother's eldest brother,
Labhu. -She is my wife, Mukho.

193
00:12:53,101 --> 00:12:54,141
Come on now.

194
00:12:54,221 --> 00:12:55,901
How about telling them
my real name?

195
00:12:55,981 --> 00:12:58,221
Dear,
I am your aunt Mukhtiar Kaur.

196
00:12:58,301 --> 00:12:59,461
Mukhtiar Kaur-ji.

197
00:13:00,141 --> 00:13:01,861
He is my eldest son.
Come forward.

198
00:13:01,941 --> 00:13:04,821
Hello. -She is his wife,
our daughter-in-law. -Hello.

199
00:13:04,861 --> 00:13:06,821
And these are their children.
Anmol and Babbu.

200
00:13:06,861 --> 00:13:08,301
That's my daughter, Jassi.
-Hello.

201
00:13:08,381 --> 00:13:10,301
Hello! -She is studying..
what does she study?

202
00:13:11,541 --> 00:13:14,781
I don't know. -Nursing. -Yes,
nursing. -The same.

203
00:13:14,861 --> 00:13:16,141
Come on in, dear.

204
00:13:16,221 --> 00:13:17,861
Let's have some tea and
refreshments. -Let's go.

205
00:13:17,901 --> 00:13:20,581
Come on. Come inside.
-Come on dear, let's go.

206
00:13:20,741 --> 00:13:21,741
Please, come.

207
00:13:21,901 --> 00:13:24,861
Dear, I hope you didn't face
any trouble on the way.

208
00:13:26,861 --> 00:13:28,901
Here mother, have some tea.

209
00:13:29,101 --> 00:13:30,381
I don't want it.

210
00:13:30,661 --> 00:13:31,941
Take it back.

211
00:13:32,061 --> 00:13:33,861
Give them to the ones
sitting outside.

212
00:13:33,901 --> 00:13:35,421
They are already having it,
mother.

213
00:13:35,541 --> 00:13:36,861
I gave them some biscuits too.

214
00:13:36,941 --> 00:13:40,021
The ones who have sidelined this
old women, may you be doomed.

215
00:13:40,621 --> 00:13:43,261
I didn't let my daughter enter
this house for 20 years.

216
00:13:43,381 --> 00:13:46,581
You have hurt my feelings
by inviting them home.

217
00:13:46,821 --> 00:13:48,261
You will never stop complaining.

218
00:13:48,541 --> 00:13:50,061
Let me know once you are done.

219
00:13:50,221 --> 00:13:51,301
Give it here.

220
00:13:52,581 --> 00:13:53,941
Oh no. Here you go.

221
00:13:54,541 --> 00:13:57,621
I won't eat till they stay here.

222
00:13:58,821 --> 00:14:00,181
As you wish, mother.

223
00:14:00,261 --> 00:14:01,661
I am such a fool.

224
00:14:01,821 --> 00:14:04,661
Why did I bother getting tea
when I know you are angry.

225
00:14:04,821 --> 00:14:07,301
It's okay. I won't make any
dinner for you then.

226
00:14:07,381 --> 00:14:09,661
It will save some dough.
-Are you going to leave or not?

227
00:14:10,661 --> 00:14:11,981
I am going, mother.

228
00:14:12,061 --> 00:14:14,141
Hello, aunt! -Tie your hair.

229
00:14:17,301 --> 00:14:20,861
Oh God, I pray that a lizard
falls into their dinner.

230
00:14:20,901 --> 00:14:22,421
I won't be eating it anyway.

231
00:14:30,741 --> 00:14:33,541
He makes noise like
a rusty engine.

232
00:14:33,701 --> 00:14:35,261
Look at that.

233
00:14:35,621 --> 00:14:38,301
Aunt, what is this?

234
00:14:38,781 --> 00:14:40,741
This tea is very sweet.

235
00:14:40,941 --> 00:14:43,661
Get me a pill for diabetes.

236
00:14:43,941 --> 00:14:44,941
Right.

237
00:14:45,741 --> 00:14:47,461
Here. Take it.

238
00:14:48,101 --> 00:14:51,581
Uncle, I am taking a sprayer.
I need to spray the field.

239
00:14:51,701 --> 00:14:54,901
Take it. They don't even
let you enjoy tea.

240
00:14:54,981 --> 00:14:57,061
People these days don't
even offer you any tea.

241
00:15:00,021 --> 00:15:01,021
Eat it, dear.

242
00:15:01,101 --> 00:15:02,781
You too have some.
-Yes, have some.

243
00:15:03,541 --> 00:15:04,781
Sister couldn't make it?

244
00:15:04,901 --> 00:15:07,181
Mom couldn't get a
leave from office.

245
00:15:09,941 --> 00:15:12,741
I am sure it gets quite cold
when it snows there.

246
00:15:13,621 --> 00:15:16,901
Then the kids must be filling
their stomachs with ice.

247
00:15:16,981 --> 00:15:18,301
Take these kids for example.

248
00:15:18,421 --> 00:15:20,421
They are always close
to the refrigerator.

249
00:15:20,541 --> 00:15:23,301
They eat the ice as soon
as it is formed.

250
00:15:24,861 --> 00:15:26,381
Driver wants biscuits.

251
00:15:26,621 --> 00:15:28,301
Give him two pieces.

252
00:15:28,381 --> 00:15:29,701
Take it, son. -Go on.

253
