Neeta, give me your Iphone,
I'll charge it.

505
00:31:42,181 --> 00:31:45,421
Wait, I'll teach you a lesson.
-Wait here.I'll teach you a lesson.

506
00:31:48,901 --> 00:31:51,701
Hello. Welcome. -Careful, son.

507
00:31:51,781 --> 00:31:53,421
Hello, Chief.

508
00:31:53,541 --> 00:31:55,941
Hello! How are you doing,
Lambardar Sahib? All good?

509
00:32:14,461 --> 00:32:18,461
Maggar, it's not the same
as Makhan had done.

510
00:32:18,981 --> 00:32:21,061
Who do uncles have
such a big egos?

511
00:32:21,941 --> 00:32:23,581
They keep troubling
because of aunts.

512
00:32:28,661 --> 00:32:31,661
Welcome, Jarnail Singh.

513
00:32:31,821 --> 00:32:33,901
Hello. -Are you alright?

514
00:32:34,541 --> 00:32:35,941
Have you never seen balloons?

515
00:32:36,021 --> 00:32:38,181
We need to go and get cold
drinks. Let's go.

516
00:32:38,261 --> 00:32:39,701
Manuri? -Yes, brother?

517
00:32:39,781 --> 00:32:41,261
Let's go and get cold drinks.

518
00:32:41,341 --> 00:32:42,861
Keep this in. I'll be right back.

519
00:32:43,301 --> 00:32:45,181
Let go of my collar.
-You let go of my shirt.

520
00:32:45,261 --> 00:32:46,381
Let go of my collar.

521
00:32:46,661 --> 00:32:48,461
You let go of my shirt.
-I'll punch you.

522
00:32:48,581 --> 00:32:51,181
Go ahead. -If you have the courage
then go ahead. -You go first.

523
00:32:51,261 --> 00:32:52,901
If you have the courage then
go ahead. -Go ahead.

524
00:32:52,981 --> 00:32:55,221
Stop talking and hit him.

525
00:32:55,301 --> 00:32:57,181
Go on.
-Today is my happy birthday.

526
00:32:57,261 --> 00:32:59,221
Otherwise, I'd show you
what I am made up of.

527
00:33:00,101 --> 00:33:01,541
You come here. -I am here.

528
00:33:02,461 --> 00:33:03,741
Beauty.. -Yes?

529
00:33:04,101 --> 00:33:06,061
They are your sisters.
-No, they are his sisters.

530
00:33:06,141 --> 00:33:09,221
I want to marry one of them and
go to Canada. Right, brother?

531
00:33:09,421 --> 00:33:13,741
How about some music, brother?

532
00:33:15,861 --> 00:33:17,821
'Maggar, what do you think?'

533
00:33:18,621 --> 00:33:19,901
'Will it work out for me?'

534
00:33:21,141 --> 00:33:26,061
'And for him?' 'Okay,
so we will each marry a sister.'

535
00:33:26,621 --> 00:33:28,621
'But he is not handsome.'

536
00:33:30,141 --> 00:33:32,861
'It's okay.
It will keep the evil eye away.'

537
00:33:43,821 --> 00:33:45,381
Mummy!

538
00:33:53,581 --> 00:33:56,141
Serve some fritters to
them as well. -Okay.

539
00:33:56,661 --> 00:33:58,581
Keep it there.

540
00:33:58,861 --> 00:34:01,701
Hello. Is everything alright?

541
00:34:02,181 --> 00:34:04,061
I need to talk to the child,
excuse me.

542
00:34:04,221 --> 00:34:06,181
All good, dear?

543
00:34:07,141 --> 00:34:08,621
It's mine.

544
00:34:09,741 --> 00:34:11,221
Eat something. -Welcome. Hello.

545
00:34:11,301 --> 00:34:13,061
I seek your blessings, aunt.

546
00:34:14,421 --> 00:34:16,021
Come here.
-Uncle didn't come along?

547
00:34:16,101 --> 00:34:18,221
The whole village is sitting
on the chair..

548
00:34:18,301 --> 00:34:19,981
..and all of you are sitting
here and cooking?

549
00:34:20,061 --> 00:34:21,901
Why didn't you get some waiters
for the function?

550
00:34:21,981 --> 00:34:23,941
It's you elders blessings.

551
00:34:24,021 --> 00:34:26,181
What else can it be?
-Didn't I explain it last night..

552
00:34:26,261 --> 00:34:28,461
..that men and women are equals?

553
00:34:28,661 --> 00:34:31,861
Don't you want to enjoy?
-Dear, there are no waiters here.

554
00:34:31,941 --> 00:34:34,661
Here you have to do everything
on your own.

555
00:34:34,821 --> 00:34:37,101
But aunt, she is talking about
our rights and welfare.

556
00:34:39,821 --> 00:34:41,661
Show it to me, sister.

557
00:34:41,741 --> 00:34:43,341
Sister.. -You have come that's
more than enough for us..

558
00:34:43,421 --> 00:34:45,141
Don't you have any shame?

559
00:34:49,021 --> 00:34:50,381
You are punishing these women.

560
00:34:50,661 --> 00:34:53,141
Either call for waiters or
order food from outside.

561
00:35:03,821 --> 00:35:05,741
Charno,
she will get us into trouble.

562
00:35:05,821 --> 00:35:07,141
Come on girls, continue working.

563
00:35:07,221 --> 00:35:08,901
Keep cooking.
Don't let the bread stick.

564
00:35:23,981 --> 00:35:25,741
I barely escaped.
-Thanks for saving me.

565
00:35:26,021 --> 00:35:29,021
She poured water over it.

566
00:35:39,581 --> 00:35:42,741
Grandma, happy birthday to you.
-To you, dear.

567
00:35:42,821 --> 00:35:44,901
Which sweet would you like the
black one or the white one?

568
00:35:44,981 --> 00:35:47,541
I like the black one, dear.

569
00:35:49,181 --> 00:35:53,101
Tell me, who sent it?
-The aunt from Canada.

570
00:35:53,461 --> 00:35:55,821
I wonder what those witches
must have spiked it with.

571
00:35:55,981 --> 00:35:58,701
Their mother sent them
here to kill me.

572
00:35:59,021 --> 00:36:00,141
Go away from here.

573
00:36:02,741 --> 00:36:03,981
Listen.. come here, dear.

574
00:36:04,661 --> 00:36:05,661
Come here.

575
00:36:06,741 --> 00:36:08,421
Which one of them is
more beautiful?

576
00:36:08,541 --> 00:36:10,421
Shall I call them here?
Do you wish to meet them?

577
00:36:10,581 --> 00:36:12,781
I am not interested. Buzz off.

578
00:36:15,981 --> 00:36:19,541
Happy birthday to you.

579
00:36:19,701 --> 00:36:23,061
Happy birthday to you.

580
00:36:23,341 --> 00:36:25,741
Happy birthday to you.

581
00:36:25,821 --> 00:36:28,181
It is very sweet.

582
00:36:28,261 --> 00:36:31,261
Happy birthday to you.

583
00:36:31,341 --> 00:36:34,101
Happy birthday to you.

584
00:36:34,181 --> 00:36:36,341
Come on wish him, or are you
here only for free food?

585
00:36:36,421 --> 00:36:40,941
Happy birthday to you.

586
00:36:41,221 --> 00:36:45,381
Happy birthday to you.

587
00:36:45,701 --> 00:36:48,101
Happy birthday to you.

588
00:36:48,261 --> 00:36:54,101
Happy birthday to you.

589
00:36:57,941 --> 00:36:59,741
God bless us all!
What has she done!

590
00:37:00,861 --> 00:37:02,101
It's okay, have some cake.

591
00:37:02,421 --> 00:37:04,341
Eat it, already.
-Everybody, eat the cake.

592
00:37:04,981 --> 00:37:06,621
Eat the cake, kids.

593
00:37:06,821 --> 00:37:08,701
Damn, what are they doing?

594
00:37:09,821 --> 00:37:12,621
Take it. -Aunt,
I too want some. -Ajaib Singh..

595
00:37:12,701 --> 00:37:15,661
..have you ordered any snacks.or
should we keep our plates down?

596
00:37:25,621 --> 00:37:26,621
We got humiliated.

597
00:37:26,861 --> 00:37:29,141
She is dangerous sober as well.

598
00:37:29,861 --> 00:37:31,341
I cannot handle her.

599
00:37:32,541 --> 00:37:33,941
I'll have to let her go.

600
00:37:34,621 --> 00:37:35,701
Take this, Jassi.

601
00:37:36,741 --> 00:37:38,821
Eat it. -The younger one is good.

602
00:37:39,901 --> 00:37:41,981
Here, give it to the girl.

603
00:37:43,141 --> 00:37:45,541
Don't make a fool of yourself.
Okay? Go.

604
00:37:45,621 --> 00:37:47,341
I won't return empty-handed
today.

605
00:37:56,781 --> 00:37:59,101
Where do you think you are going?
-To give lunch to Nicole.

606
00:37:59,701 --> 00:38:00,781
Keep it down.

607
00:38:01,741 --> 00:38:02,741
Yes?

608
00:38:04,301 --> 00:38:05,381
What..

609
00:38:07,381 --> 00:38:08,381
Come on.

610
00:38:09,861 --> 00:38:11,861
Let go of my hair!
Don't punch me.

611
00:38:14,981 --> 00:38:17,781
How many times have I told you?
Don't you understand?

612
00:38:17,861 --> 00:38:19,421
If you try to come
closer to Nicole..

613
00:38:19,541 --> 00:38:21,101
..henceforth then
you're done for.

614
00:38:21,701 --> 00:38:22,821
Go and give it to her.

615
00:38:25,181 --> 00:38:26,421
Idiot.

616
00:38:27,341 --> 00:38:29,581
She is very rude to
her brother-in-law.

617
00:38:31,461 --> 00:38:32,461
Please eat it.

618
00:38:36,061 --> 00:38:38,661
Thank you for caring for me.

619
00:38:39,141 --> 00:38:41,301
Who says it's care?
I just don't like him.

620
00:38:41,741 --> 00:38:45,141
Kash, you care for me.
You just don't accept it.

621
00:38:45,541 --> 00:38:47,461
Okay tell me, what my fault is.

622
00:38:47,861 --> 00:38:51,261
Mom divorced dad, I didn't.

623
00:38:52,941 --> 00:38:55,141
I didn't get dad's love.

624
00:38:55,341 --> 00:38:57,341
At least let me get some
of my sister's love now.

625
00:39:04,101 --> 00:39:05,101
Your phone.

626
00:39:11,741 --> 00:39:12,981
Okay.

627
00:39:13,061 --> 00:39:14,461
Manjeeti's call?

628
00:39:15,581 --> 00:39:18,181
Hello, mom.
How are you? -Very good.

629
00:39:18,261 --> 00:39:19,821
How did you like my family?

630
00:39:19,981 --> 00:39:22,661
Oh mom,
your mother is one angry lady.

631
00:39:22,741 --> 00:39:23,941
We both haven't met her yet..

632
00:39:24,021 --> 00:39:25,701
..out of the fear of
being thrashed.

633
00:39:25,781 --> 00:39:28,781
No,
mother has always been like that.

634
00:39:28,901 --> 00:39:30,301
But she doesn't hurt anyone.

635
00:39:30,621 --> 00:39:33,701
She had beaten me up just once.

636
00:39:33,861 --> 00:39:35,981
When I had worn that
flower-embroidered dress.

637
00:39:36,141 --> 00:39:39,421
The flower-embroidered dress?
-Yes, ask her about it.

638
00:39:39,941 --> 00:39:41,221
Okay then, bye. Good night.

639
00:39:41,581 --> 00:39:43,341
You should go meet your grandma.

640
00:39:43,901 --> 00:39:45,141
Okay, mom, bye.

641
00:39:46,221 --> 00:39:47,861
Kash, shall we go meet grandma?

642
00:39:48,701 --> 00:39:50,221
No. -Please!

643
00:39:50,301 --> 00:39:51,421
No. -Please!

644
00:39:51,541 --> 00:39:53,261
You want to get thrashed?
-She won't beat us up.

645
00:39:53,341 --> 00:39:54,381
Come on, let's go.

646
00:39:54,461 --> 00:39:56,101
Hey boy, give me my stick back.

647
00:39:56,181 --> 00:39:58,901
This whole family is
after my blood.

648
00:39:59,541 --> 00:40:00,541
Hey..

649
00:40:04,821 --> 00:40:06,421
Should I do this to you?

650
00:40:12,861 --> 00:40:14,461
Grandma, here is your stick.

651
00:40:14,701 --> 00:40:17,981
For your own well-being,
go back the way you came.

652
00:40:19,341 --> 00:40:21,261
Mom said she is rude but
she doesn't hurt anyone.

653
00:40:22,381 --> 00:40:23,901
Grandma, at least hear us out.

654
00:40:23,981 --> 00:40:25,701
I'll beat you with my stick,
leave.

655
00:40:26,101 --> 00:40:27,981
Grandma, what grudge are
you holding against us?

656
00:40:28,341 --> 00:40:29,941
We are here just to talk to you.

657
00:40:30,061 --> 00:40:31,541
Talk about what?

658
00:40:31,861 --> 00:40:33,381
The things your mother
taught you?

659
00:40:34,261 --> 00:40:35,781
Fine, don't talk.

660
00:40:35,941 --> 00:40:38,421
At least tell us what is the
mystery of the flower dress?

661
00:40:38,541 --> 00:40:40,301
Mom said we should talk
to you about it.

662
00:40:40,381 --> 00:40:43,301
Don't trouble me.
Go away from here.

663
00:40:44,141 --> 00:40:45,301
Oh God!

664
00:40:50,341 --> 00:40:51,581
Grandma..

665
00:40:52,861 --> 00:40:55,221
Mom loves you a lot.

666
00:41:04,661 --> 00:41:10,661
"You cannot even imagine
how much I love you."

667
00:41:10,741 --> 00:41:12,621
Ask him to sit outside.

668
00:41:13,461 --> 00:41:15,581
Go and sit with Nicole.

669
00:41:15,661 --> 00:41:16,821
I won't.

670
00:41:17,621 --> 00:41:19,781
Don't make me hit you.
Why won't you leave?

671
00:41:19,861 --> 00:41:21,621
Our family could have a million
things to discuss in private.

672
00:41:21,701 --> 00:41:24,381
Come on, leave.
-Go away. -Take this.

673
00:41:31,741 --> 00:41:35,221
Look brother,
you are the eldest..

674
00:41:35,421 --> 00:41:37,301
..t would be better if
you spoke to them.

675
00:41:37,381 --> 00:41:38,901
It won't look good if I say it.

676
00:41:38,981 --> 00:41:40,461
It's not about seniority.

677
00:41:40,581 --> 00:41:42,901
You know better,
what will I tell them?

678
00:41:42,981 --> 00:41:45,261
Come on brother,
it's no use delaying.

679
00:41:45,541 --> 00:41:47,421
We will have to talk to them.
-Right.

680
00:41:47,541 --> 00:41:50,021
What will the villagers say if
the younger brother does this..

681
00:41:50,101 --> 00:41:51,861
..in the presence of an
elder brother? Yes.

682
00:41:52,941 --> 00:41:55,421
Villagers? Fine then give
me an anti-anxiety pill.

683
00:41:58,181 --> 00:41:59,221
What's up, bro!

684
00:42:00,101 --> 00:42:02,581
Come on, have a seat.

685
00:42:04,341 --> 00:42:06,261
How are you? -Good.

686
00:42:06,981 --> 00:42:09,181
What your girl did with
you was not right.

687
00:42:10,181 --> 00:42:12,221
She shouldn't have been so harsh,
right? -Which one?

688
00:42:12,341 --> 00:42:13,981
You don't need to
hide it from me.

689
00:42:14,061 --> 00:42:15,461
I saw her pulling your hair.

690
00:42:16,021 --> 00:42:17,741
You two will soon get married.

691
00:42:17,821 --> 00:42:19,701
After marriage, people tend
to get a little shameless.

692
00:42:19,781 --> 00:42:20,981
But it is not right now.

693
00:42:21,061 --> 00:42:23,821
No, brother. I am going to get
married to the younger one.

694
00:42:24,221 --> 00:42:26,661
I never liked the older one. Yes.

695
00:42:27,381 --> 00:42:29,621
The younger one? -Yes.
She is beautiful, isn't she?

696
00:42:30,061 --> 00:42:32,421
No, no, no. -Why? What's wrong?

697
00:42:33,861 --> 00:42:35,421
It's something not
to be discussed.

698
00:42:35,541 --> 00:42:36,901
You should go to sleep,
my brother.

699
00:42:36,981 --> 00:42:38,821
No please, tell me what's wrong.

700
00:42:42,141 --> 00:42:44,821
Look nothing stays hidden
from drivers. -Yes.

701
00:42:45,061 --> 00:42:47,341
I saw her having tobacco.

702
00:42:47,981 --> 00:42:49,661
For real? -Yes.

703
00:42:50,461 --> 00:42:52,261
She has tobacco? -Yes.

704
00:42:52,701 --> 00:42:54,381
Oh, this is great.

705
00:42:54,461 --> 00:42:56,461
And I feared I won't get
tobacco in Canada.

706
00:42:57,701 --> 00:42:59,701
Both of us will have it together.
Wonderful.

707
00:43:00,261 --> 00:43:02,421
Stand up, get up.

708
00:43:04,181 --> 00:43:05,941
He is here to give me
a sleepless night.

709
00:43:06,461 --> 00:43:07,581
Get lost from here.

710
00:43:07,661 --> 00:43:09,301
You are the one who asked
me to come here.

711
00:43:09,381 --> 00:43:11,421
I asked you to,
like you are some big shot.

712
00:43:16,421 --> 00:43:17,901
Everyone's so nice.

713
00:43:18,701 --> 00:43:20,421
They love us a lot.

714
00:43:21,141 --> 00:43:23,461
I just wonder why grandma
is so upset.

715
00:43:24,461 --> 00:43:26,261
Everyone else is very nice.

716
00:43:27,461 --> 00:43:29,621
We missed these things in Canada.

717
00:43:31,781 --> 00:43:34,421
Mom and dad's fights
separated us.

718
00:43:35,421 --> 00:43:38,341
We learnt what a family
is after coming here.

719
00:43:39,061 --> 00:43:41,581
I wish mom and dad too
were here with us.

720
00:43:42,661 --> 00:43:44,301
Aunt, would you like some sugar?

721
00:43:44,861 --> 00:43:45,981
No!

722
00:43:46,421 --> 00:43:48,941
You're my cute little
Barbie Doll.

723
00:43:51,941 --> 00:43:53,461
How cute is she!

724
00:43:53,901 --> 00:43:56,781
Come on girls,
drink your milk and go to sleep.

725
00:43:56,861 --> 00:43:58,421
We will go to the market
in the morning..

726
00:43:58,541 --> 00:43:59,701
..where you can buy
Indian dresses.

727
00:43:59,781 --> 00:44:01,941
Aunt,
I don't wear Indian dresses.

728
00:44:02,061 --> 00:44:04,901
It's okay dear, you can buy
anklets instead. Go to sleep, girls.

729
00:44:04,981 --> 00:44:07,301
Come, kid, your mother is looking
for you downstairs. -No.

730
00:44:07,381 --> 00:44:09,621
Come with me. Drink the milk
before it gets cold.

731
00:44:09,701 --> 00:44:11,581
Come on, grandma.
-Shut up. Come with me.

732
00:44:14,741 --> 00:44:15,821
Cheers!

733
00:44:24,781 --> 00:44:27,221
Brother,
show us some bright colours.

734
00:44:27,301 --> 00:44:28,941
Show us pure silk dresses.

735
00:44:30,781 --> 00:44:32,221
Here's one in orange.

736
00:44:32,901 --> 00:44:33,901
It's very good.

737
00:44:33,981 --> 00:44:35,661
Karmo, we need to buy knickers
for your father too.

738
00:44:35,741 --> 00:44:38,141
They have gone tight.
-Okay. -Here's another one.

739
00:44:39,301 --> 00:44:42,861
Oh no, embellishments on knickers
will cause rash.

740
00:44:42,941 --> 00:44:44,221
This is an Indian dress.

741
00:44:45,061 --> 00:44:46,821
Then show us something good.

742
00:44:47,421 --> 00:44:49,141
Hey why don't you order
some cold drinks?

743
00:44:49,221 --> 00:44:50,221
These girls have come from
abroad. -This one..

744
00:44:50,301 --> 00:44:54,341
Get four and a half cold drinks!
-Half for whom? -For me.

745
00:44:54,421 --> 00:44:55,541
Damn you.

746
00:44:55,781 --> 00:44:58,661
Show me a embroidered veil.

747
00:44:58,821 --> 00:45:00,301
Big flowers or small flowers?

748
00:45:01,781 --> 00:45:03,101
Any would do.

749
00:45:03,861 --> 00:45:05,461
It should just look good on her.

750
00:45:06,661 --> 00:45:08,941
Show me that one, the one in
blue. -The one at the end?

751
00:45:10,141 --> 00:45:11,781
She will tear it apart.

752
00:45:12,821 --> 00:45:13,941
The one on this end.

753
00:45:14,901 --> 00:45:16,861
It's an excellent piece.

754
00:45:17,381 --> 00:45:18,741
She is your sister-in-law.

755
00:45:19,421 --> 00:45:21,301
I am talking about the veil,
brother.

756
00:45:28,021 --> 00:45:31,221
Today, you will meet your end!
-Stop it!

757
00:45:31,301 --> 00:45:33,461
I won't spare you!
-Now look at them!

758
00:45:33,581 --> 00:45:37,061
There they are! -Give it to me!

759
00:45:37,141 --> 00:45:40,821
I want the chocolates!
-They brought chocolates for us!

760
00:45:41,061 --> 00:45:43,821
You want all of it!
You witch! -Yes, sister?

761
00:45:44,301 --> 00:45:46,421
Here, I have brought anklets.

762
00:45:48,341 --> 00:45:50,901
And I also brought a
few Indian dresses.

763
00:45:51,181 --> 00:45:52,861
The one with flowers on them.

764
00:45:53,181 --> 00:45:56,421
They are so beautiful.
-Aunt brought them.

765
00:45:56,861 --> 00:45:59,421
We will wear the dresses
with flowers on them.

766
00:45:59,621 --> 00:46:01,261
I dare anyone to do
anything they want.

767
00:46:01,381 --> 00:46:03,261
I'll get them stitched
tomorrow itself. -Yes.

768
00:46:03,341 --> 00:46:05,261
They are beautiful, aren't they?
-Yes, they are.

769
00:46:30,741 --> 00:46:33,741
What is this? -Mother.
-What have you been upto?

770
00:46:33,821 --> 00:46:36,101
Mother, aunt from the city
got it stitched for me.

771
00:46:36,181 --> 00:46:39,301
You want to be fashionable!
You want to wear flowery dresses!

772
00:46:39,821 --> 00:46:42,821
I'll kill you if you wear
this dress again.

773
00:46:43,061 --> 00:46:45,381
She wants to dress
like actresses!

774
00:47:09,821 --> 00:47:13,461
Dear, brother Labhu wanted
to talk to you.

775
00:47:14,261 --> 00:47:15,661
Huh?

776
00:47:19,061 --> 00:47:20,141
Yes. -Yes.

777
00:47:20,981 --> 00:47:22,661
Dear,
I have been wondering whether..

778
00:47:22,741 --> 00:47:24,261
..or not to discuss
this with you.

779
00:47:24,621 --> 00:47:26,261
You know how we are
a big happy family.

780
00:47:26,341 --> 00:47:27,621
We like together peacefully.

781
00:47:27,701 --> 00:47:30,701
We don't fight over
land like others.

782
00:47:31,181 --> 00:47:34,381
But who knows about the future.
Look, mother has aged.

783
00:47:34,621 --> 00:47:37,381
I too don't keep well. -So, we all
sat together and decided that..

784
00:47:37,621 --> 00:47:39,221
..we should all take
our shares now.

785
00:47:39,621 --> 00:47:41,421
We don't want our kids to
fight in the future.

786
00:47:41,541 --> 00:47:44,541
And then dear, all of you are
well settled in Canada.

787
00:47:44,741 --> 00:47:48,701
Right? -As for us, we are bound
to suffer here. -Yes.

788
00:47:51,621 --> 00:47:54,781
So I thought that as you
are already here..

789
00:47:54,901 --> 00:47:57,621
..why don't we all take our
shares and end this matter?

790
00:47:58,061 --> 00:48:01,461
Dear, as you know this is what
has been happening since ages..

791
00:48:01,581 --> 00:48:04,141
..land always belonged
to the sons.

792
00:48:04,341 --> 00:48:06,421
Right? -We had invited sister.

793
00:48:06,541 --> 00:48:08,581
But she sent you two. -Yes.

794
00:48:11,821 --> 00:48:13,261
Let us know what you want to do.

795
00:48:14,381 --> 00:48:15,381
Okay.

796
00:48:35,701 --> 00:48:37,381
We have made their will.

797
00:48:37,741 --> 00:48:39,741
If sister manages to come
then it will be great.

798
00:48:39,821 --> 00:48:41,061
We have everything ready.

799
00:48:41,461 --> 00:48:42,621
Okay?

800
00:48:52,461 --> 00:48:54,461
Hey hello!
What are you doing here?

801
00:48:54,581 --> 00:48:56,061
Father, what are you doing here?

802
00:48:57,221 --> 00:49:00,821
I have come here to take a form
to open an ostrich farm.

803
00:49:01,061 --> 00:49:02,261
What are you doing here?

804
00:49:02,981 --> 00:49:06,541
I am here with some Canadian
passengers.

805
00:49:06,621 --> 00:49:07,741
They have rented uncle's car.

806
00:49:07,821 --> 00:49:09,061
If they have rented
the car then your..

807
00:49:09,141 --> 00:49:11,821
..job is only drive them around.
-Why are you carrying their bags?

808
00:49:11,901 --> 00:49:15,381
Father, don't you always say
that we should help others.

809
00:49:15,461 --> 00:49:19,461
Wonderful. My son is very smart.
-Then do one thing..

810
00:49:19,581 --> 00:49:22,421
..carry this sack and help me
load it on the mini bus.

811
00:49:23,381 --> 00:49:25,221
Father, you are still
stuck on a mini bus?

812
00:49:25,661 --> 00:49:28,061
Here I am making plans
to take a flight.

813
00:49:29,461 --> 00:49:30,461
Well done.

814
00:49:30,981 --> 00:49:32,941
I wonder what will happen
of this new generation.

815
00:49:33,181 --> 00:49:35,741
I like a fool have come here to
take a form for ostriches.

816
00:49:36,061 --> 00:49:37,941
No one would give them forms
even for poultry.

817
00:49:41,181 --> 00:49:43,061
Maggar, my father too is
here, in the court.

818
00:49:43,461 --> 00:49:45,661
We should get your sister-in-law
touch his feet, right?

819
00:49:45,781 --> 00:49:47,821
I think you too love dogs.

820
00:49:48,181 --> 00:49:51,061
No, I don't like them.
I am scared of them.

821
00:49:51,181 --> 00:49:55,581
You need to take 12 shots
if a dog bites you.

822
00:49:55,821 --> 00:49:58,381
People keep pampering them
for no reason. Idiots.

823
00:49:58,461 --> 00:50:01,741
Stupid. Do you know how
kindhearted dogs are?

824
00:50:02,021 --> 00:50:03,581
They are so loyal.

825
00:50:04,021 --> 00:50:05,741
They love more than humans.

826
00:50:06,421 --> 00:50:07,661
Heartless people.

827
00:50:08,461 --> 00:50:10,941
I will surely get into trouble
because of your kind some day.

828
00:50:29,941 --> 00:50:31,581
Hello, mom? How are you, Nicole?

829
00:50:31,661 --> 00:50:33,421
Mom,
you know what happened today?

830
00:50:35,021 --> 00:50:36,381
Hello mom, it's me, Kash.

831
00:50:36,621 --> 00:50:38,461
Yes Kashmir,
are you liking it out there?

832
00:50:38,701 --> 00:50:40,821
Like it?
I don't wish to come back.

833
00:50:40,901 --> 00:50:42,421
But I hate you. -Why?

834
00:50:42,741 --> 00:50:45,221
Couldn't you tell us sooner that
your family is so nice?

835
00:50:45,941 --> 00:50:47,461
You know we went for
shopping today.

836
00:50:47,701 --> 00:50:49,861
Aunt forced me to
buy anklets too.

837
00:50:50,181 --> 00:50:51,781
And you know what the
best part was?

838
00:50:51,861 --> 00:50:52,901
I bought so many Indian dresses.

839
00:50:52,981 --> 00:50:55,941
The ones with flower embroidery
on it. -Wow, that's great.

840
00:50:56,581 --> 00:51:00,301
Okay, everyone is staring at me.
We'll call you later.

841
00:51:00,901 --> 00:51:04,661
Okay, bye.
-Okay. Fine, enjoy. Bye.

842
00:51:09,821 --> 00:51:11,541
We won't tell mom what
happened here.

843
00:51:11,621 --> 00:51:12,661
She's so happy.

844
00:51:13,101 --> 00:51:15,421
Her family thought about
her after so many years.

845
00:51:15,661 --> 00:51:17,061
Why should we spoil her mood?

846
00:51:18,461 --> 00:51:19,461
Right.

847
00:51:20,101 --> 00:51:21,621
Sugarcoated people, eh?

848
00:51:21,981 --> 00:51:23,901
They couldn't take about
it directly with mom.

849
00:51:24,101 --> 00:51:25,941
What do we have to do
with their property?

850
00:51:27,061 --> 00:51:29,701
Looks like our parents
are very good.

851
00:51:29,781 --> 00:51:31,661
At least whatever they do they
do it in front of us.

852
00:51:31,741 --> 00:51:33,301
At least they aren't
double-faced.

853
00:51:34,821 --> 00:51:37,661
I think they are the ones
troubling grandma.

854
00:51:38,861 --> 00:51:41,941
She is so upfront. If she is
angry then she is angry.

855
00:51:54,221 --> 00:51:56,701
Here you go, Amrik. Set them up.

856
00:52:23,821 --> 00:52:24,821
Here, Neeta.

857
00:52:26,181 --> 00:52:27,421
Take it. -No, sister.

858
00:52:28,341 --> 00:52:29,341
Take it.

859
00:52:30,261 --> 00:52:33,901
Tell your friend that your sister
bought you an Iphone.

860
00:52:37,821 --> 00:52:39,701
No.. -Here.

861
00:52:40,461 --> 00:52:41,541
Look at this.

862
00:52:44,701 --> 00:52:45,701
Do it.

863
00:52:52,021 --> 00:52:54,741
Okay? -Yes. -You won't feel scared
now, will you? -No, I won't.

864
00:52:56,821 --> 00:53:00,821
Will you take me to Canada
after I grow up?

865
00:53:01,341 --> 00:53:02,341
Okay.

866
00:53:18,181 --> 00:53:20,541
Take this, girl. Here's yours.

867
00:53:21,301 --> 00:53:23,061
I didn't have change.

868
00:53:23,461 --> 00:53:25,821
You have to pretend
before the world.

869
00:53:25,981 --> 00:53:27,621
I don't know whether
or not we will..

870
00:53:27,701 --> 00:53:29,061
..get to see each other again.

871
00:53:29,261 --> 00:53:31,301
It will be between you
and your uncles.

872
00:53:31,581 --> 00:53:34,661
You are always welcomed here.
How does it concern me?

873
00:53:41,301 --> 00:53:42,301
Take this.

874
00:53:43,581 --> 00:53:46,461
Tell your mother to wear this
flower-embroidered dress.

875
00:53:46,661 --> 00:53:48,461
I was anyway going to use
it to mop the floor.

876
00:54:04,941 --> 00:54:11,941
"Strange are the hues of life,
o' mother.."

877
00:54:12,181 --> 00:54:15,421
"It feels like the heart
is being pulled apart.."

878
00:54:15,701 --> 00:54:19,021
"As we part ways, o' mother."

879
00:54:19,341 --> 00:54:22,701
"Moonlight is no different
than me.."

880
00:54:22,861 --> 00:54:26,861
"Even the nights don't belong
to me, o' mother."

881
00:54:30,101 --> 00:54:37,101
"Tell me how do I wipe the tears
and smile, o' mother."

882
00:54:37,341 --> 00:54:45,301
"Tell me how do I wipe the tears
and smile, o' mother."

883
00:54:59,101 --> 00:55:06,261
"Mother, tell me, why is
affection such a bad thing?"

884
00:55:06,461 --> 00:55:13,181
"Why do we love anyone,
why does the heart ache?"

885
00:55:13,661 --> 00:55:21,141
"Get me something to sooth
my soul, o' mother."

886
00:55:21,261 --> 00:55:28,381
"Tell me how do I wipe the tears
and smile, o' mother."

887
00:55:28,541 --> 00:55:35,581
"Tell me how do I wipe the tears
and smile, o' mother."

888
00:55:35,701 --> 00:55:39,021
"Tell me how, o' mother."

889
00:56:07,741 --> 00:56:11,301
"Mother, I have contracted
a strange illness."

890
00:56:11,381 --> 00:56:15,301
"I don't know when
I contracted it."

891
00:56:15,381 --> 00:56:22,021
"Why does my heart want to
jump out of my chest?"

892
00:56:22,621 --> 00:56:24,821
"After being invited..

893
00:56:24,901 --> 00:56:29,541
..the door was closed at my face,
o' mother."

894
00:56:29,621 --> 00:56:31,341
Grandma sent a dress for mom.

895
00:56:32,981 --> 00:56:34,941
Mom didn't send anything
for grandma.

896
00:56:39,741 --> 00:56:42,061
Stupid, mom sent us for her.

897
00:56:43,541 --> 00:56:44,821
Yeah.

898
00:56:45,901 --> 00:56:46,981
Amrik? -Yes?

899
00:56:47,061 --> 00:56:48,141
Turn the car around.

900
00:56:48,541 --> 00:56:49,541
Okay.

901
00:56:51,901 --> 00:56:59,061
"Tell me how do I wipe the tears
and smile, o' mother."

902
00:56:59,141 --> 00:57:06,141
"Tell me how do I wipe the tears
and smile, o' mother."

903
00:57:06,421 --> 00:57:10,341
I too was wondering, you haven't
even toured Punjab as yet.

904
00:57:10,581 --> 00:57:12,141
How can you just leave!

905
00:57:12,461 --> 00:57:15,941
I know it is my love that
made you stay back.

906
00:57:16,381 --> 00:57:19,981
Shut up. -Look, you shouldn't
be rude to the driver.

907
00:57:20,341 --> 00:57:23,221
They sometimes drive straight
into a river when angry.

908
00:57:24,341 --> 00:57:26,861
But you don't need to worry.
-I am not a driver.

909
00:57:27,061 --> 00:57:28,221
I am the owner.

910
00:57:28,301 --> 00:57:30,941
We have many cars on the road.

911
00:57:57,941 --> 00:57:59,381
It's not our fault.

912
00:57:59,461 --> 00:58:01,101
I too don't talk to Manjeeti.

913
00:58:01,181 --> 00:58:02,301
Give me a high five.

914
00:58:02,941 --> 00:58:04,461
Come with us, grandma.
Please. -Yes.

915
00:58:04,581 --> 00:58:05,821
Please. -It will be a lot of fun.

916
00:58:05,901 --> 00:58:08,861
You will be happy. -I am happy.
-It's not like I have been shot.

917
00:58:08,941 --> 00:58:11,581
Liar! Your eyes are still red.

918
00:58:23,141 --> 00:58:24,181
Hello, uncle.

919
00:58:24,621 --> 00:58:26,221
What's wrong?
Did grandma pass away?

920
00:58:26,661 --> 00:58:28,101
Shut up.

921
00:58:29,741 --> 00:58:31,421
Uncle!

922
00:58:31,541 --> 00:58:33,421
Give me the sprayer.
I need to spray the fields.

923
00:58:33,541 --> 00:58:36,341
Does our sprayer kill
more insects?

924
00:58:36,421 --> 00:58:38,221
You can take it today,
but never ask for it again.

925
00:58:38,301 --> 00:58:39,781
Otherwise, I will throw you out.

926
00:58:40,341 --> 00:58:43,101
Resham, give him the sprayer.

927
00:58:44,621 --> 00:58:46,981
She is just pretending to be
angry. She will come with us.

928
00:58:47,021 --> 00:58:48,581
Come on, let's go.
-Come on, please.

929
00:58:48,661 --> 00:58:50,221
Let's go, let's go.
-Please, please.

930
00:58:50,741 --> 00:58:53,621
Come on. -Take her bag. -Why
are you dragging me along?

931
00:58:56,941 --> 00:58:57,941
Here you go.

932
00:59:11,621 --> 00:59:13,061
Don't worry, uncle.

933
00:59:13,141 --> 00:59:14,901
We will be back in 5-7 days.

934
00:59:14,981 --> 00:59:17,141
It will be a good change
for grandma as well.

935
00:59:17,221 --> 00:59:20,661
It's okay, dear. You are very
smart to convince her.

936
00:59:20,741 --> 00:59:22,661
God bless you. -Bye, aunt. -Bye.

937
00:59:22,941 --> 00:59:24,021
Okay, bye.

938
00:59:24,621 --> 00:59:25,781
You are leaving?

939
00:59:35,541 --> 00:59:36,981
Here's the sprayer.

940
00:59:37,541 --> 00:59:38,541
Sprayer for what?

941
00:59:38,901 --> 00:59:40,781
To hell with such a sprayer.

942
00:59:40,861 --> 00:59:42,581
These sprays have
destroyed Punjab.

943
00:59:42,661 --> 00:59:43,941
You should eat these
poisonous grains.

944
00:59:43,981 --> 00:59:45,941
I will do organic farmer now.

945
00:59:47,061 --> 00:59:48,061
Bye, uncle.

946
00:59:48,261 --> 00:59:49,461
I too will get going now.

947
00:59:49,741 --> 00:59:50,941
Bye, aunt.

948
00:59:58,941 --> 01:00:00,781
Grandma,
you don't need to worry at all.

949
01:00:00,861 --> 01:00:03,261
We will enjoy life to the fullest
in the next five days.

950
01:00:04,621 --> 01:00:08,381
Your decision to take grandma
on a tour has won my heart.

951
01:00:08,461 --> 01:00:09,861
Like your heart is
a world cup that..

952
01:00:09,941 --> 01:00:12,741
..winning it is an achievement.
-Shut up and drive.

953
01:00:12,821 --> 01:00:14,181
"Won his heart."

954
01:00:28,181 --> 01:00:30,101
Oh no, what is this room?

955
01:00:30,381 --> 01:00:31,981
Grandma, this is an elevator.

956
01:00:32,061 --> 01:00:34,861
It will lift you up very quickly.
-Let her lift your grandmother.

957
01:00:34,941 --> 01:00:36,221
I don't want to die so soon.

958
01:00:36,301 --> 01:00:37,621
Come on. -Let's go, grandma.

959
01:00:37,701 --> 01:00:39,901
I don't want to enter it.
-Nothing will happen.

960
01:00:39,981 --> 01:00:42,101
Let's go.
-I don't want to enter it.

961
01:00:42,181 --> 01:00:45,381
I will feel suffocated.
-Nothing will happen. Let's go.

962
01:00:45,901 --> 01:00:47,541
My sons have locked me in a room.

963
01:00:47,621 --> 01:00:49,141
And you are locking
me up in here.

964
01:00:49,301 --> 01:00:51,661
Grandma,
it will take us up quickly.

965
01:00:52,221 --> 01:00:53,981
Nothing happened. You are fine.

966
01:00:54,421 --> 01:00:55,581
Nothing happened.

967
01:00:56,301 --> 01:00:59,181
These idiots have blankets
on the floor.

968
01:01:00,421 --> 01:01:02,941
That's a carpet.
It's called a carpet.

969
01:01:03,181 --> 01:01:04,341
Tell me about it.

970
01:01:04,901 --> 01:01:06,581
It's over here as well.

971
01:01:06,701 --> 01:01:09,061
It's everywhere, grandma.

972
01:01:12,581 --> 01:01:14,701
Welcome home, grandma.

973
01:01:15,821 --> 01:01:16,821
Come in.

974
01:01:29,301 --> 01:01:30,941
Such a big room!

975
01:01:31,101 --> 01:01:32,861
Grandma,
come here, look at the view.

976
01:01:36,701 --> 01:01:38,341
No, I will fall down.

977
01:01:38,861 --> 01:01:41,061
There's a glass window here.
-Did you like the room?

978
01:01:41,141 --> 01:01:43,661
I have never even dreamed of such
a beautiful place, dear.

979
01:01:44,101 --> 01:01:46,461
Grandma, look over there,
that's the bathtub.

980
01:01:48,981 --> 01:01:51,861
Oh God, such a beautiful bathtub!

981
01:01:52,061 --> 01:01:54,941
In villages, many houses don't
even have such beautiful halls.

982
01:01:55,261 --> 01:01:56,261
Right.

983
01:01:56,341 --> 01:01:58,301
It is actually a place where
one can bathe, dear?

984
01:01:58,381 --> 01:02:00,421
Yes, and you too will bathe here.

985
01:02:00,581 --> 01:02:01,581
Be ready.

986
01:02:29,581 --> 01:02:31,581
Get in grandma,
you will have a lot of fun.

987
01:02:31,661 --> 01:02:32,901
No, I won't get in there.

988
01:02:32,981 --> 01:02:35,261
Grandma, you will get a message.
Come on, get in.

989
01:02:35,341 --> 01:02:36,981
I will drown in it, dear.

990
01:02:37,181 --> 01:02:38,941
Get in, grandma. -No.

991
01:02:39,021 --> 01:02:40,301
No, dear. I won't get in.

992
01:02:40,381 --> 01:02:41,621
Come on, grandma.

993
