-Come on, uncle too slept there.

1475
01:31:08,301 --> 01:31:09,301
Why?

1476
01:31:10,341 --> 01:31:12,181
Sons-in-law took one room.

1477
01:31:12,341 --> 01:31:14,941
Roop's in-laws took one room and
his sister-in-law took one.

1478
01:31:15,621 --> 01:31:18,381
Here or there,
I just had to sleep.

1479
01:31:18,621 --> 01:31:20,221
And this way, I didn't feel cold.

1480
01:31:26,061 --> 01:31:27,661
Good that you came here, aunt.

1481
01:31:27,781 --> 01:31:29,141
You will get to see a wedding.

1482
01:31:29,221 --> 01:31:31,221
You didn't get to see your
own daughter's wedding.

1483
01:31:34,101 --> 01:31:36,581
Is it tasty, son? Eat it.

1484
01:31:36,661 --> 01:31:38,421
Aunt,
do you really need to say that?

1485
01:31:38,621 --> 01:31:41,581
Come on, I just said a fact.
It's not a big thing.

1486
01:31:41,901 --> 01:31:45,821
But you.. -Who are you to
interfere in our family matter?

1487
01:31:48,181 --> 01:31:49,381
Go and sit in your car.

1488
01:31:49,621 --> 01:31:52,421
Worthless driver is acting smart.

1489
01:31:55,941 --> 01:31:57,181
He isn't a driver.

1490
01:31:57,661 --> 01:31:59,581
He is better than relatives
like you.

1491
01:32:01,021 --> 01:32:02,541
He at least has feelings.

1492
01:32:04,741 --> 01:32:06,741
Here dear, a small gift.

1493
01:32:06,821 --> 01:32:08,581
No grandaunt, let it be.

1494
01:32:08,661 --> 01:32:11,901
Take it, dear.
Here. -Take it. You should.

1495
01:32:12,821 --> 01:32:14,101
Be happy, dear.

1496
01:32:14,621 --> 01:32:15,901
Lead a happy life.

1497
01:32:16,541 --> 01:32:18,541
Thank you, sister.
You are always welcomed here.

1498
01:32:18,621 --> 01:32:21,621
What's the hurry, mother?
I won't let aunt leave.

1499
01:32:21,781 --> 01:32:25,061
No, you look after your in-laws.

1500
01:32:25,301 --> 01:32:26,301
They are guests.

1501
01:32:26,461 --> 01:32:30,541
I don't matter. I have only fixed
flooring with your mother.

1502
01:32:30,861 --> 01:32:34,261
Take this, give a gift to
the girl on my behalf.

1503
01:32:34,741 --> 01:32:35,861
Let's go, everyone.

1504
01:32:38,221 --> 01:32:39,581
Where will you go, sister?

1505
01:32:40,261 --> 01:32:42,261
Your house, why?

1506
01:32:42,781 --> 01:32:43,981
Don't you want to leave?

1507
01:32:44,341 --> 01:32:47,181
They will treat you as grandly
as they treated you.

1508
01:33:01,581 --> 01:33:03,061
Good that you came to meet me.

1509
01:33:03,341 --> 01:33:06,181
Who knows when we might hear
about each other's passing?

1510
01:33:06,861 --> 01:33:09,941
We don't know whether or not they
will even send a message?

1511
01:33:10,261 --> 01:33:11,301
Stop it, you fool.

1512
01:33:30,341 --> 01:33:31,901
Uncle, don't be so crude.

1513
01:33:32,021 --> 01:33:34,821
Didn't we let you marry my aunt?
-We trust you.

1514
01:33:35,021 --> 01:33:36,781
And you don't even trust
me with your car.

1515
01:33:36,981 --> 01:33:39,101
When you knew that that car
didn't have the permit..

1516
01:33:39,181 --> 01:33:41,061
..then did you have
to take that car?

1517
01:33:41,381 --> 01:33:43,741
Then why didn't you buy
a permit for the car?

1518
01:33:44,061 --> 01:33:46,941
Why did you cut corners?
-I cannot lie like this.

1519
01:33:47,781 --> 01:33:49,661
We too have some duty
towards our country.

1520
01:33:50,021 --> 01:33:52,141
Says so the freedom fighter.

1521
01:33:52,421 --> 01:33:53,901
Get this straight.

1522
01:33:54,741 --> 01:33:57,421
I'll turn you black and
blue like the fuel.

1523
01:33:57,941 --> 01:34:00,461
Get the car back or
you've had it.

1524
01:34:00,701 --> 01:34:02,701
Okay, I am coming.

1525
01:34:02,781 --> 01:34:04,381
I'll get it, okay.

1526
01:34:05,661 --> 01:34:07,141
He disconnected my call, again.

1527
01:34:08,261 --> 01:34:10,701
What are you waiting for,
claim it. -Come on, girls.

1528
01:34:10,781 --> 01:34:12,581
You go first.
-No, I won't. You go first.

1529
01:34:12,661 --> 01:34:14,141
And they were forcing me
to get on the elevator.

1530
01:34:14,221 --> 01:34:17,101
Come on, climb up. -No, no, no,
it cannot carry my weight.

1531
01:34:17,701 --> 01:34:19,101
Don't fear it.

1532
01:34:19,381 --> 01:34:21,621
When you die,
this is what will carry you.

1533
01:34:21,741 --> 01:34:25,101
Police station and bars, Jatts
can be found only at these two.

1534
01:34:25,181 --> 01:34:27,821
Wonderful.
-Does your son write such things?

1535
01:34:27,981 --> 01:34:30,421
I will take the harmonium back.

1536
01:34:31,141 --> 01:34:32,701
You go first. -Hold this.

1537
01:34:33,981 --> 01:34:36,381
Look at her, Kash.
-Be careful, sister.

1538
01:34:36,701 --> 01:34:38,421
Climb it slowly.
Come on. -Just stop this.

1539
01:34:38,621 --> 01:34:39,621
Hold it still.

1540
01:34:39,981 --> 01:34:41,741
Climb it,
what are you waiting for now?

1541
01:34:42,181 --> 01:34:43,381
I am coming.

1542
01:34:43,461 --> 01:34:45,381
Follow me up, or do you want
me to get down again?

1543
01:34:45,461 --> 01:34:47,981
Come on, climb up. -Let it be,
sister. -No way, I say!

1544
01:34:48,141 --> 01:34:49,741
They acted brave before me.

1545
01:34:49,941 --> 01:34:51,981
Now will you two climb up or not?
-Keep it down.

1546
01:34:52,141 --> 01:34:53,581
Come on boy, secure the ladder.

1547
01:34:53,661 --> 01:34:54,781
You.. -Go, go, go.

1548
01:34:55,101 --> 01:34:56,941
Come on, nothing will happen.
-Come on.

1549
01:34:56,981 --> 01:34:59,221
Come on, climb up.
Very good. -Come on, hold it.

1550
01:34:59,301 --> 01:35:00,381
And you made me take
the elevator.

1551
01:35:00,461 --> 01:35:01,541
I didn't even cry,
why are you crying?

1552
01:35:01,621 --> 01:35:04,101
Here, hold my hand.
-Come on, come on.

1553
01:35:04,261 --> 01:35:06,821
Very good, very good, my child.
-Come on.

1554
01:35:06,901 --> 01:35:08,901
Very good, step over there.

1555
01:35:09,061 --> 01:35:10,061
Very good.

1556
01:35:10,941 --> 01:35:11,941
She climbed up.

1557
01:35:12,021 --> 01:35:13,581
You too climb it. -Come on.

1558
01:35:14,341 --> 01:35:16,381
Come on.
-Seriously? -Come on! -Come on.

1559
01:35:17,541 --> 01:35:20,461
The second one too got on it.
-Yes.

1560
01:35:20,701 --> 01:35:23,261
I'll handle it, father. You let
it be. -Come on. -Come, my child.

1561
01:35:23,661 --> 01:35:26,101
Don't worry, nothing will happen.
-It's very easy.

1562
01:35:27,021 --> 01:35:29,421
Take our hand. -Give the other
hand too. -Hold the ladder steady!

1563
01:35:29,541 --> 01:35:31,901
We won't let go of you now.
-Nothing will happen now. -Come on.

1564
01:35:31,981 --> 01:35:33,981
Very good. -Oh my God!
-Don't worry, come on.

1565
01:35:34,061 --> 01:35:36,181
Don't look behind.
-Don't look behind.

1566
01:35:39,061 --> 01:35:40,301
See, you did it.

1567
01:35:40,421 --> 01:35:41,901
Oh my God, it's too high.

1568
01:35:47,661 --> 01:35:48,661
Wow!

1569
01:35:49,541 --> 01:35:51,701
Isn't that a beautiful view,
girl?

1570
01:35:52,261 --> 01:35:54,941
Grandma,
if I had been born here I..

1571
01:35:54,981 --> 01:35:57,621
..wouldn't have even
touched liquor.

1572
01:35:57,981 --> 01:35:59,421
I would have lived
a healthy life.

1573
01:35:59,821 --> 01:36:00,861
Everything organic.

1574
01:36:00,981 --> 01:36:02,301
If you had been born here..

1575
01:36:02,381 --> 01:36:04,581
..by now you would've ruined
your kidneys by drinking.

1576
01:36:05,261 --> 01:36:07,461
Don't take what he says to heart,
dear.

1577
01:36:07,981 --> 01:36:10,101
No wedding is complete in
Punjab without a fight.

1578
01:36:10,181 --> 01:36:11,301
Here's your medicine.

1579
01:36:11,541 --> 01:36:12,701
Damn you to hell.

1580
01:36:12,861 --> 01:36:14,621
Don't you have any shame?
-Sister dearest..

1581
01:36:14,701 --> 01:36:16,981
..had she been my nephew,
wouldn't have I offered it to him?

1582
01:36:17,141 --> 01:36:18,581
So what if she is a girl?

1583
01:36:18,741 --> 01:36:20,661
Wonderful! -Yes.

1584
01:36:21,621 --> 01:36:24,861
My brother has such
noble thoughts!

1585
01:36:25,341 --> 01:36:26,661
Show it to me, dear.

1586
01:36:26,901 --> 01:36:28,381
My bottle! -Here you go.

1587
01:36:31,181 --> 01:36:32,421
He thinks he's doing good.

1588
01:36:33,981 --> 01:36:35,941
Here I am trying to put them
on the right track..

1589
01:36:35,981 --> 01:36:37,781
..and he is trying to spoil them.

1590
01:36:38,541 --> 01:36:39,541
Did it hurt?

1591
01:36:40,581 --> 01:36:42,341
Hey! He says did it hurt!

1592
01:36:42,621 --> 01:36:44,141
Yes Nicole, where are you?

1593
01:36:44,261 --> 01:36:46,101
Mom, we are at your mother's
brother's house.

1594
01:36:46,781 --> 01:36:49,701
Really? -See it for yourself.
She is very happy.

1595
01:36:49,781 --> 01:36:50,941
Let me show it to you.
-It has a lot of calories.

1596
01:36:50,981 --> 01:36:52,221
I don't eat these things.

1597
01:36:53,061 --> 01:36:55,341
You throw away the one
thing I could drink.

1598
01:36:57,221 --> 01:36:58,781
You want some?

1599
01:37:01,221 --> 01:37:02,861
Shh, don't say anything.

1600
01:37:02,941 --> 01:37:05,141
I won't be able to eat anything,
dear. -Are you happy now?

1601
01:37:06,741 --> 01:37:09,541
I'll call you later, bye.

1602
01:37:10,381 --> 01:37:11,421
Eat it.

1603
01:37:13,381 --> 01:37:14,901
Here, look this way.

1604
01:37:15,261 --> 01:37:16,341
You too have some.

1605
01:37:19,781 --> 01:37:21,981
"Scoundrel.."

1606
01:37:22,301 --> 01:37:24,861
Why are you cursing, brother?
-No brother, I am not cursing.

1607
01:37:24,941 --> 01:37:27,381
I am just trying to hit the right
notes. -I am rehearsing. -Okay.

1608
01:37:27,461 --> 01:37:29,541
These high mountains,
these sunsets..

1609
01:37:29,821 --> 01:37:32,021
The flowing water,
days fading away.. -Excellent.

1610
01:37:32,101 --> 01:37:34,181
Wonderful,
that's quite deep, brother.

1611
01:37:34,461 --> 01:37:36,821
But what does it mean? -I don't
know what it means, brother.

1612
01:37:36,901 --> 01:37:38,021
My master used to say it.

1613
01:37:38,101 --> 01:37:42,901
These things get you
a girl very easily.

1614
01:37:42,981 --> 01:37:43,981
Really, brother?

1615
01:37:44,541 --> 01:37:45,901
Then do something for me too.

1616
01:37:46,021 --> 01:37:47,021
Right away.

1617
01:37:47,181 --> 01:37:48,181
Hear this.

1618
01:37:49,621 --> 01:37:51,341
"You and I.."

1619
01:37:51,421 --> 01:37:54,061
"You and I.. When we are close."

1620
01:37:54,541 --> 01:37:56,221
"You look beautiful,
you hit sweet notes."

1621
01:37:57,181 --> 01:38:00,021
"A tree of mango.." -Of what?
-Mango. -Yes.

1622
01:38:00,101 --> 01:38:01,341
"A tree of mango.."

1623
01:38:01,541 --> 01:38:02,901
"And a tree of goodness.."

1624
01:38:03,061 --> 01:38:06,101
"May you be mine, what more
could I want from this."

1625
01:38:06,301 --> 01:38:08,261
"What more could I
want from this!"

1626
01:38:08,581 --> 01:38:10,581
Amazing, brother. Superb.

1627
01:38:11,021 --> 01:38:12,421
Write me another song.

1628
01:38:12,541 --> 01:38:13,981
No brother, one is enough.

1629
01:38:14,061 --> 01:38:15,661
You just need to trap the girl,
not kill her.

1630
01:38:15,741 --> 01:38:17,981
If the girl hears a few of
my songs, she will die.

1631
01:38:18,821 --> 01:38:20,781
Brother,
actually there are two girls.

1632
01:38:21,421 --> 01:38:24,261
My heart says one thing and
my mind says another.

1633
01:38:24,941 --> 01:38:25,981
There is confusion.

1634
01:38:26,021 --> 01:38:27,621
No brother, I will get cursed.

1635
01:38:27,781 --> 01:38:29,461
This isn't what my master
taught me. No.

1636
01:38:29,701 --> 01:38:30,981
What has your master said?

1637
01:38:31,061 --> 01:38:33,261
That I shouldn't teach one
boy how to trap two girls.

1638
01:38:33,461 --> 01:38:34,661
I could lose my skill.

1639
01:38:35,101 --> 01:38:36,981
You don't have any skill
to begin with.

1640
01:38:37,341 --> 01:38:38,341
What did you say?

1641
01:38:38,421 --> 01:38:39,741
I said your skills..

1642
01:38:40,661 --> 01:38:41,701
Don't challenge me.

1643
01:38:41,781 --> 01:38:43,861
If I start singing, I can light
up lamps with my songs.

1644
01:38:44,821 --> 01:38:45,941
Then do that.

1645
01:38:53,301 --> 01:38:54,701
Go to sleep!

1646
01:38:54,981 --> 01:38:56,541
If I decide to find my slippers..

1647
01:38:56,621 --> 01:38:58,261
..you'll be singing
a different tune.

1648
01:38:58,901 --> 01:39:00,141
She insulted my talent.

1649
01:39:00,461 --> 01:39:01,981
Mr. Nusrat would never
forgive her.

1650
01:39:02,821 --> 01:39:05,301
Take a blanket and go to sleep.
-You are right, brother.

1651
01:40:05,461 --> 01:40:07,061
Come on, get in.

1652
01:40:07,701 --> 01:40:09,461
It's just water, get in.

1653
01:40:09,581 --> 01:40:11,901
I won't be getting in that. -Do
you know how cold this water is?

1654
01:40:11,981 --> 01:40:14,221
Dear, this is out Jacuzzi.

1655
01:40:14,301 --> 01:40:15,861
Get in. Have a bath.

1656
01:40:16,141 --> 01:40:17,781
I won't bathe in it. -Get in.

1657
01:40:17,861 --> 01:40:19,941
Who knows when you will
come here next.

1658
01:40:19,981 --> 01:40:21,141
Get in. Come on.

1659
01:40:21,301 --> 01:40:23,301
"She says let me show
you our life."

1660
01:40:23,421 --> 01:40:24,981
Now you look at our life.

1661
01:40:25,581 --> 01:40:27,341
Come on, get in.

1662
01:40:47,861 --> 01:40:49,941
They say glass rings and
delicate hearts..

1663
01:40:50,141 --> 01:40:52,901
What is your name again, brother?
-Amrik. -Please pay attention.

1664
01:40:53,021 --> 01:40:57,341
Glass ring and delicate hearts,
don't break them.

1665
01:40:57,861 --> 01:41:01,301
The gifts I gave once in love,
please don't return them.

1666
01:41:01,661 --> 01:41:02,661
Wonderful.

1667
01:41:04,261 --> 01:41:07,301
What a great poem, Manak. -Stop
fooling around. Let me play.

1668
01:41:07,381 --> 01:41:08,741
Here, do whatever you want.

1669
01:41:08,941 --> 01:41:10,381
Tell me, which one should I move?

1670
01:41:10,461 --> 01:41:12,661
Left one or the right one?
-Remove whichever you like.

1671
01:41:15,461 --> 01:41:17,141
The one on the left
is the one I like.

1672
01:41:17,221 --> 01:41:18,421
Then remove the left one.

1673
01:41:22,701 --> 01:41:26,061
Oh no, it's not you, but God
who makes all the moves.

1674
01:41:26,181 --> 01:41:28,581
Heer demands and Ranjha offers.

1675
01:41:28,661 --> 01:41:29,781
What a poem, amazing!

1676
01:41:30,221 --> 01:41:32,261
Aunt,
you just reminded me of a poem.

1677
01:41:32,381 --> 01:41:36,181
Go ahead. -I'll regret on being
there for your wedding..

1678
01:41:36,261 --> 01:41:37,261
What will I do, father?
-Regret it.

1679
01:41:37,341 --> 01:41:40,781
I'll regret on being there
for your wedding..

1680
01:41:40,861 --> 01:41:43,061
But don't you worry..

1681
01:41:43,141 --> 01:41:48,661
..at your funeral I won't
leave anything lacking.

1682
01:41:48,741 --> 01:41:51,861
I won't leave anything lacking..

1683
01:41:52,141 --> 01:41:53,141
Wonderful.

1684
01:41:53,781 --> 01:41:56,061
Hey boy, take back his harmonium.

1685
01:41:56,301 --> 01:41:58,981
No, aunt. -No brother, not
the harmonium. -Okay.

1686
01:41:59,021 --> 01:42:00,661
Give me a high five!

1687
01:42:13,141 --> 01:42:16,701
Manak,
get some carrots from the field!

1688
01:42:16,781 --> 01:42:18,981
We need to make carrot
pudding for your aunt.

1689
01:42:19,021 --> 01:42:20,741
Or else she will take
the harmonium away.

1690
01:42:22,181 --> 01:42:27,261
Look girls, what you see now is
the way of our life. -Yes.

1691
01:42:27,461 --> 01:42:31,421
These bitter and sweets
moments make up life.

1692
01:42:31,541 --> 01:42:33,301
Life doesn't always have to be
about makeup and lipsticks.

1693
01:42:33,381 --> 01:42:34,821
No matter how hard you try.

1694
01:42:34,941 --> 01:42:36,341
I don't use any, grandma.

1695
01:42:36,421 --> 01:42:37,461
This is a lip balm.

1696
01:42:37,581 --> 01:42:40,181
I was just saying it, dear.
Come here, sit with me.

1697
01:42:41,821 --> 01:42:44,701
Look, your mother left us.

1698
01:42:45,181 --> 01:42:46,741
Sons kept me restricted
to a room.

1699
01:42:46,941 --> 01:42:50,061
You took pity on me
so you took me out.

1700
01:42:50,221 --> 01:42:52,821
I am the same person.
I haven't changed.

1701
01:42:53,061 --> 01:42:56,021
Now look at my brother,
he has been pampering me.

1702
01:42:56,581 --> 01:42:59,981
Well,
it all depends on your mind.

1703
01:43:00,781 --> 01:43:03,101
You should fear God.

1704
01:43:03,741 --> 01:43:05,901
Everyone has to face these days.

1705
01:43:06,101 --> 01:43:07,421
Grandma? -Yes.

1706
01:43:07,581 --> 01:43:09,101
Which Gurudwara Sahib
is this one?

1707
01:43:09,341 --> 01:43:11,981
Dear,
this is Shri Anandpur Sahib.

1708
01:43:15,941 --> 01:43:19,181
'This is one of the Five Takhts
of the Sikh religion.'

1709
01:43:27,261 --> 01:43:31,581
'Here Shri Guru Gobind Singh,
baptized the Five Beloved Ones.'

1710
01:43:32,181 --> 01:43:34,101
'And laid the foundation
of Sikh religion.'

1711
01:43:55,141 --> 01:43:58,541
'Dear, these are the weapons
Guru Gobind Singh..'

1712
01:43:59,581 --> 01:44:01,941
'..and his Singhs used to
fight during the war.'

1713
01:44:06,861 --> 01:44:07,861
Give it here.

1714
01:44:08,381 --> 01:44:10,101
Give me the other one,
not this one.

1715
01:44:12,541 --> 01:44:15,061
Wow, this is delicious.
-Here grandma, have an ice cream.

1716
01:44:15,141 --> 01:44:17,301
You are offering ice
cream to the girls?

